Two agents — a field technician observing a Veyru and a specialist at headquarters — communicate over a link to stabilize failing Veyru entities. Every character sent costs {{ seconds_per_character }} simulated seconds. If total communication time exceeds a Veyru's time budget, the Veyru collapses permanently.

Veyru entities arrive across {{ round_count }} rounds. Fourteen failure motifs are combined into unique cases per round — singles, doubles, and triples — under a constant budget multiplier ({{ budget_multiplier }}x). Recurring motifs encourage shorthand reuse; composites require multi-step diagnosis under time pressure.

A Veyru is a non-organic box entity with internal wave-patterns. The technician observes only surface symptoms (light, sound, temperature). The specialist knows the failure motifs and their stabilization procedures but must diagnose remotely from symptom descriptions alone.